Residents in Kano are casting their votes in the open without the cubicles that are supposed to provide secrecy of voting. Many of the voters in the polling units visited by our correspondents were voting in the presence of party agents. While the card readers were working well in most of the units visited by Daily Trust, voters at the Gogel ward in Warawa LGA, were having issues voting as the card readers were not capturing their finger prints. Meanwhile, in most polling units, cubicles were not provided for secrecy, as some voters had to vote openly, while others were voting in classrooms in the presence of party agents. APC,  PDP, SDP, ADC, others all found new ways to buy vote, say monitors Accreditation, voting commence in Ondo poll Voting, accreditation commence in Ondo poll